demand.

The package exposes three entry points that all share the same
\code{method} argument:
\itemize{
\item \code{\link[=compress_posterior]{compress_posterior()}} for a posterior draws matrix or any object
convertible via the \code{posterior} package.
\item \code{\link[=compress_fit]{compress_fit()}} for a \code{cmdstanr} \code{CmdStanMCMC} fit.
\item \code{\link[=compress_brmsfit]{compress_brmsfit()}} for a \code{brms::brmsfit} fit (cmdstanr backend).
}

A convenience wrapper \code{\link[=compress_sccomp]{compress_sccomp()}} is also provided for \code{sccomp}
fits, which store the underlying cmdstanr fit in \code{attr(x, "fit")}.

Currently supported methods (see \code{?compression_methods}):
\itemize{
\item \code{"mclust"}: Gaussian mixture model via \code{\link[mclust:Mclust]{mclust::Mclust()}}.
\item \code{"mvdens_gmm"}: Gaussian mixture model via the \code{mvdens} package
(suggested).
\item \code{"mvdens_kde"}: kernel density estimate via the \code{mvdens} package
(suggested).
}

All compress wrappers return an S3 object of class
\code{posterior_compressed} (with a method-specific subclass) that can be
fed to \code{\link[=sample_posterior]{sample_posterior()}} and \code{\link[=density_posterior]{density_posterior()}}.
